The paper discusses the consensus algorithms used in blockchain technology, which involves cryptography and distributed systems (cs.CR). It also discusses the performance and security of these algorithms, which are important aspects of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also uses a taxonomy to analyze the algorithms, which is a common technique in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of different issues in consensus algorithms, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper analyzes over a hundred cryptocurrencies, which involves cybersecurity and cryptography (cs.CY).
